Webhook Integration
1. Configure Webhook
bash
curl -X POST https://riskfortress.com/api/webhooks \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "url": "https://yourcompany.com/webhook/riskfortress",
    "events": ["threat_detected", "report_ready", "service_completed"],
    "secret": "your_webhook_secret"
  }'
2. Webhook Events
Threat Detected:

json
{
  "event": "threat_detected",
  "data": {
    "threatId": "T-2024-001",
    "title": "New threat detected",
    "severity": "high",
    "sector": "industrial",
    "detectedAt": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
  },
  "signature": "sha256=<signature>"
}
Report Ready:

json
{
  "event": "report_ready",
  "data": {
    "reportId": "R-2024-001",
    "type": "due_diligence",
    "title": "Land Verification Report",
    "url": "https://riskfortress.com/reports/R-2024-001",
    "generatedAt": "2024-01-15T14:00:00Z"
  }
}
3. Verify Webhook Signature
javascript
const crypto = require('crypto')

function verifySignature(payload, signature, secret) {
  const hmac = crypto.createHmac('sha256', secret)
  const digest = hmac.update(JSON.stringify(payload)).digest('hex')
  return `sha256=${digest}` === signature
}
Error Handling
HTTP Status Codes
200 - Success

201 - Created

400 - Bad Request

401 - Unauthorized

403 - Forbidden

404 - Not Found

429 - Too Many Requests

500 - Internal Server Error

Error Response Format
json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "Invalid input data",
    "details": {
      "email": ["Invalid email format"]
    },
    "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z"
  }
}
SDKs & Libraries
JavaScript/TypeScript SDK
bash
npm install @riskfortress/sdk
typescript
import { RiskFortress } from '@riskfortress/sdk'

const client = new RiskFortress({
  apiKey: 'your-api-key',
  baseUrl: 'https://riskfortress.com/api'
})

// Submit intake
const intake = await client.submitIntake({
  company: 'Example Corp',
  email: 'api@examplecorp.com',
  // ... other fields
})

// Get threats
const threats = await client.getThreats({
  sector: 'industrial',
  severity: 'high'
})
